CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 10, 1959, pg. A2 reads: "Nominating Committee - The newly elected nominating committee, which will choose a slate of candidates for positions on the executive board of the Pittsburgh Branch NAACP is shown above. They are Mrs. Carrie Reid, Mrs. Louise Payne, Mrs. Sophia Nelson, McKinley Tomlin, Malvin Goode, Atty. Henry R. Smith Jr. and Atty. Donald Stocks.  Members of the committee not shown are Mrs. Edythe Perkins, Frank E. Bolden, William Ford and Mrs. Elvira Marks. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: NAACP nominating committee, seated from left: Carrie Reid, Louise Payne, Sophia Nelson; standing: McKinley Tomlin, Malvin "Mal" Goode, Atty. Henry R. Smith Jr., and Atty. Donald Stocks, gathered in Ebenezer Baptist church for NAACP membership meeting
